recipes.name: Spicy Chicken Tacos
recipes.description: Delicious and spicy chicken tacos with fresh salsa.
recipes.instructions:
1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. 
2. Add chicken and cook until browned. 
3. Add bell peppers, onion, and jalapeno pepper. Cook until vegetables are tender. 
4. Season with chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper. 
5. Warm tortillas in a separate skillet. 
6. Fill tortillas with chicken mixture, cheese, salsa, and cilantro. 
7. Serve hot.

recipes.name: Vegetable Stir-Fry
recipes.description: Healthy and colorful vegetable stir-fry with tofu.
recipes.instructions:
1. Marinate tofu in soy sauce and sesame oil. 
2. Heat vegetable oil in a wok or skillet over high heat. 
3. Add garlic and cook until fragrant. 
4. Add tofu and cook until golden brown. 
5. Add bell peppers, broccoli, carrot, snap peas, and mushrooms. Stir-fry until vegetables are tender. 
6. In a small bowl, mix hoisin sauce, rice vinegar, and cornstarch. Pour over stir-fry and cook until sauce thickens. 
7. Serve over cooked rice.

recipes.name: Classic Margherita Pizza
recipes.description: Authentic Italian pizza topped with fresh tomatoes, mozzarella, and basil.
recipes.instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 450F (230C). 
2. Place pizza crust on a baking sheet. 
3. Spread pizza sauce evenly over the crust. 
4. Arrange tomato slices and mozzarella cheese on top. 
5. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. 
6. Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted. 
7. Remove from oven and sprinkle with fresh basil leaves. 
8. Slice and serve hot.

recipes.name: Creamy Mushroom Risotto
recipes.description: Rich and creamy Italian risotto with mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
recipes.instructions:
1. In a saucepan, heat the broth over low heat. 
2. In a separate large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. 
3. Add onion and garlic, cook until softened. 
4. Add mushrooms and cook until they release their liquid. 
5. Stir in the rice and cook for 1 minute. 
6. Add white wine and cook until absorbed. 
7. Gradually add hot broth, stirring frequently, until rice is cooked and creamy. 
8. Stir in Parmesan cheese and parsley. Season with salt and pepper. 
9. Serve hot.

recipes.name: Blueberry Pancakes
recipes.description: Fluffy pancakes filled with fresh blueberries, perfect for breakfast.
recipes.instructions:
1. In a large bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
2. In another bowl, whisk together buttermilk, egg, and melted butter.
3. Pour wet ingredients into dry ingredients and mix until just combined.
4. Gently fold in blueberries.
5. Heat a lightly greased skillet or griddle over medium heat.
6. Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake.
7. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown.
8. Serve hot with maple syrup.
